from collections import deque
x,y,z,n,m,s,t=map(int,input().split())
g=[[]for _ in range(x+y+z)]
for i in range(n):
  a,b=map(int,input().split())
  g[a-1].append(b+x-1)
  g[b+x-1].append(a-1)
  if i==s-1:
    p,q=a-1,b+x-1
for j in range(m):
  a,b=map(int, input().split())
  g[a+x-1].append(b+x+y-1)
  g[b+x+y-1].append(a+x-1)
  if j==t-1:
    u,v=a+x-1,b+x+y-1
d=[-2]*(x+y+z)
d[p],d[q]=0,0
q=deque([p,q])
while q:
  p = q.popleft()
  for node in g[p]:
    if d[node]==-2:
      q.append(node)
      d[node]=d[p]+1
print(min(d[u],d[v])+1)

import sys
sys.setrecursionlimit(10**7)

dice = [[6,3,1,4],
        [2,0,2,0],
        [1,3,6,4],
        [5,0,5,0]]
H,W = map(int,input().split())
s = list(input() for _ in range(H))
board = [[0]*W for _ in range(H)]

def dfs(x,y):
    board[x][y] = 1
    for dx,dy in [[0,-1],[0,1],[1,0],[-1,0]]:
        if not(0 <= dx+x < H and 0 <= dy+y < W):
            continue
        if(board[x+dx][y+dy] == 1):
            continue

        if s[x+dx][y+dy] == str(dice[(x+dx)%4][(y+dy)%4]):
            dfs(dx+x,dy+y)

dfs(0,0)
print(["NO","YES"][board[-1][-1]])
